      "content": "The idea that safety nets are a primary disincentive is a common talking point, but it ignores the reality of economic necessity. These programs are crucial stabilizers that prevent poverty and allow individuals to weather economic downturns. To frame them purely as a disincentive is to ignore the fundamental societal contract that supports a functioning economy.",
      "source": "target",
